{\pard\sb200\sa200\b\fs28 1. INTRODUCTION\par}

{\pard\sb100\b\fs24 1.1 Purpose and Scope\par}
{\pard\sa100 This document outlines the testing methodology for validating the SecureScan vulnerability scanner, with particular emphasis on the newly integrated CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) detection capabilities. The test plan encompasses functional, integration, performance, and security testing to ensure system reliability and accuracy.\par}

{\pard\sb100\b\fs24 1.2 Objectives\par}
{\pard The primary testing objectives are to:\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  Validate CVE detection accuracy against known vulnerabilities (target: >90%)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  Verify API integration with external vulnerability databases (NVD, Vulners)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  Ensure system performance under operational load conditions\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  Confirm data integrity and security compliance\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  Validate user interface consistency and accessibility\par}
\par

{\pard\sb200\sa200\b\fs28 2. TEST STRATEGY\par}

{\pard\sb100\b\fs24 2.1 Testing Hierarchy\par}
{\pard\sa100 The testing approach follows a hierarchical structure progressing from unit-level validation to system-wide acceptance testing:\par}

{\trowd\trgaph108\trleft-108
\cellx2880\cellx5760\cellx8640\cellx11520
{\pard\intbl\qc\b Level\cell Coverage Target\cell Tools\cell\row}
{\pard\intbl Unit Testing\cell 80%\cell pytest, Jest\cell\row}
{\pard\intbl Integration Testing\cell 90%\cell pytest, Postman\cell\row}
{\pard\intbl System Testing\cell 100%\cell Manual, automated scripts\cell\row}
{\pard\intbl Acceptance Testing\cell 100%\cell User scenarios\cell\row}
}
\par

{\pard\sb100\b\fs24 2.2 Test Categories\par}
{\pard Testing activities are categorized by functional domain:\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  \b Functional Testing:\b0  Core feature validation (Priority: High)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  \b API Testing:\b0  RESTful endpoint verification (Priority: High)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  \b Performance Testing:\b0  Load and response time analysis (Priority: Medium)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  \b Security Testing:\b0  Vulnerability and penetration testing (Priority: High)\par}
{\pard\li360 \bullet  \b Usability Testing:\b0  User interface evaluation (Priority: Medium)\par}
\par

